Ace Magashule court case: Who is Cupcake? JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary General, Ace Magashule's supporters came out in numbers to support him when he appeared at the Bloemfontein Magistrate's Court on Friday. Magashule is facing 21 fraud, corruption, and money-laundering charges, linked to the R255-million Free State asbestos audit project. READ: Only ANC branches can tell me to step aside: Magashule One of his supporters caused a frenzy on social media after her response to an eNCA question about the identity of the person mentioned on her placard. The short clip has created a buzz on social media.